## Key Insights
- Game has massive internal randomness: same code, same seed → 0.00 or 19.19
- Economy protection helps but can't fully prevent wipeouts (stochastic)
- 2 scramblers better than 1, but 3rd aligner better than 3rd scrambler
- 2 miners is the sweet spot for late game
- True average across many runs is ~3-5 (not >10 yet)
- Biggest lever: patrol staleness (35 is optimal)
- 2nd scrambler at step 1000-3000 range is good
- Deposit threshold 20 is good, higher hurt
- Dynamic pressure scaling based on economy is critical
- Running many games in parallel causes CPU contention and worse results

